[
    {
        "text": "Hello. This is 6 Minute English from",
        "start": 7.406,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "BBC Learning English. I’m Neil.",
        "start": 9.326,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "And I’m Sam.",
        "start": 11.886,
        "duration": 1.752
    },
    {
        "text": "These days, our lives are filled with",
        "start": 13.638,
        "duration": 2.088
    },
    {
        "text": "devices that were unimaginable only",
        "start": 15.726,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "a few years ago – the sorts of things",
        "start": 17.966,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "you read about in science-fiction novels,",
        "start": 20.126,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "but never thought you’d own.",
        "start": 22.206,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "Yes, like those robots that vacuum your",
        "start": 24.126,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "floor or voice-activated lights –",
        "start": 26.606,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "we call many of these things ‘smart tech’.",
        "start": 29.886,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "But while they can help with the little",
        "start": 33.246,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "tasks at home, some people are",
        "start": 35.086,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": "wondering whether they can help",
        "start": 36.846,
        "duration": 1.36
    },
    {
        "text": "fight climate change.",
        "start": 38.206,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "Yes, smart homes, regulating things",
        "start": 39.886,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "like the temperature, are a step in the",
        "start": 42.366,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "right direction. Using AI to learn when",
        "start": 44.606,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "the house is occupied and the optimal",
        "start": 47.726,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "time to fire up the heating, is one way",
        "start": 50.286,
        "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
        "text": "to limit wasteful use of resources.",
        "start": 53.326,
        "duration": 3.188
    },
    {
        "text": "The problem comes from the origin",
        "start": 56.514,
        "duration": 1.932
    },
    {
        "text": "of the energy which powers these home",
        "start": 58.446,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "systems. If it’s fossil fuels, then digging",
        "start": 60.526,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "them up – an informal way of saying",
        "start": 63.326,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "removing something from the earth -",
        "start": 65.246,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "and burning them creates carbon",
        "start": 67.086,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "emissions.",
        "start": 69.086,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "I suppose that’s why many people",
        "start": 70.286,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "are trying to find more renewable",
        "start": 72.366,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "forms of energy to reduce their",
        "start": 74.446,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "carbon footprint.",
        "start": 76.366,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "Well, it’s interesting that you",
        "start": 78.046,
        "duration": 1.2
    },
    {
        "text": "mentioned carbon footprint,",
        "start": 79.246,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "because my question is about that",
        "start": 80.766,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "today. How many tonnes of carbon dioxide",
        "start": 82.446,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "are humans responsible for emitting into",
        "start": 85.966,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "the atmosphere every year? Is it more than:",
        "start": 88.126,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "a) 30 billion",
        "start": 91.326,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "b) 40 billion; or",
        "start": 93.326,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "c) 50 billion?",
        "start": 95.406,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "Well, Neil, that all sounds like a lot to",
        "start": 97.566,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "me, but I’ll go straight down the middle",
        "start": 99.966,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "and say b – 40 billion tonnes.",
        "start": 101.966,
        "duration": 3.356
    },
    {
        "text": "OK, Sam, we’ll find out the correct",
        "start": 105.322,
        "duration": 1.524
    },
    {
        "text": "answer at the end of the programme.",
        "start": 106.846,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "So you mentioned earlier that people",
        "start": 108.926,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": "are looking into ways to use more",
        "start": 110.686,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "renewable energy, but there are also",
        "start": 112.526,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "some problems with that form",
        "start": 114.766,
        "duration": 1.28
    },
    {
        "text": "of energy production.",
        "start": 116.046,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "Yes – for example many of these",
        "start": 117.726,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "technologies rely on certain weather",
        "start": 119.566,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "conditions, which affect the level",
        "start": 121.886,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "of energy production.",
        "start": 124.446,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "Dr Enass Abo-Hamed, CEO of H2go,",
        "start": 126.286,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "is working on a project on Orkney,",
        "start": 130.606,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "an island off the coast of Scotland,",
        "start": 132.686,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "testing ways of storing renewable",
        "start": 134.686,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "forms of energy. Here she is on BBC",
        "start": 136.766,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "World Service programme Crowd Science,",
        "start": 139.886,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "speaking with Graihagh Jackson, talking",
        "start": 141.966,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "about the limitations of renewable energy sources.",
        "start": 144.046,
        "duration": 4.4
    },
    {
        "text": "Renewable energy is intermittent by",
        "start": 148.446,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "its nature because it’s dependant",
        "start": 150.126,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": "and relying on the weather. When",
        "start": 151.886,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "the Sun shines and when the wind blows,",
        "start": 154.686,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "and these by nature are not",
        "start": 157.566,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "24-hour 7 reliable constant.",
        "start": 159.486,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "And that means that demand doesn’t",
        "start": 162.126,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "always meet supply of renewables –",
        "start": 163.646,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "it can mean that we get blackouts,",
        "start": 165.486,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "but on the other hand, when the Sun",
        "start": 167.646,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "is up and we are producing all that",
        "start": 170.446,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "power or when the wind is blowing",
        "start": 172.126,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "and were producing that power, we",
        "start": 173.566,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "might not be able to use that energy -",
        "start": 175.246,
        "duration": 1.28
    },
    {
        "text": "There’s no demand for it and so it’s wasted.",
        "start": 176.526,
        "duration": 4.24
    },
    {
        "text": "So, Dr Enass Abo-Hamed said the",
        "start": 180.766,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "renewable energy is intermittent,",
        "start": 183.486,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "which means that something is",
        "start": 186.446,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "not continuous and has many breaks.",
        "start": 187.966,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "She also said that because there",
        "start": 191.486,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "isn’t always a steady stream of energy,",
        "start": 193.086,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "we can get blackouts –",
        "start": 195.806,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "periods of time without energy.",
        "start": 197.326,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "People like Dr Enass Abo-Hamed",
        "start": 199.966,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "are trying to find solutions to make",
        "start": 201.886,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "renewable energy storage devices –",
        "start": 203.806,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "which would make the supply",
        "start": 206.286,
        "duration": 1.2
    },
    {
        "text": "of energy more constant.",
        "start": 207.486,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "Smart tech can also help with this",
        "start": 210.126,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "problem with renewable sources.",
        "start": 212.046,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, of course, not only can computers",
        "start": 214.206,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "be used to design efficient models,",
        "start": 216.446,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "but smart tech can also be used to",
        "start": 218.286,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "improve performance after things like",
        "start": 220.366,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "wind turbines have been installed.",
        "start": 222.526,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "Here is Graihagh Jackson, science broadcaster",
        "start": 224.846,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "and podcaster, speaking about how",
        "start": 227.166,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "smart tech can improve efficiency",
        "start": 229.246,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "on BBC World Service programme, Crowd Science:",
        "start": 231.726,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Some engineers use something",
        "start": 235.726,
        "duration": 1.2
    },
    {
        "text": "called a digital twin. This is really",
        "start": 236.926,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "interesting, actually. This is where",
        "start": 238.846,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "lots of sensors are attached to the",
        "start": 240.366,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": "wind turbine, so it can be modelled",
        "start": 242.126,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "on a computer in real time. And then,",
        "start": 244.766,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "using machine learning, you can then",
        "start": 247.406,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "simulate what’s happening to the wind",
        "start": 249.406,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "turbine in specific weather conditions.",
        "start": 251.886,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "And this is important because it means",
        "start": 254.046,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "they can make sure they’re",
        "start": 256.286,
        "duration": 1.12
    },
    {
        "text": "performing their best.",
        "start": 257.406,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "Graihagh Jackson used the expression",
        "start": 259.566,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "in real time, which means without delay or live.",
        "start": 261.406,
        "duration": 4.658
    },
    {
        "text": "She also mentioned machine learning,",
        "start": 266.064,
        "duration": 2.462
    },
    {
        "text": "which is the way computers change their",
        "start": 268.526,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "behaviour based on data they collected.",
        "start": 270.606,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "And she also said simulate –",
        "start": 274.286,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "produce a computer model of something.",
        "start": 275.966,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "So, while there are issues with",
        "start": 278.766,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": "the reliability of the source of",
        "start": 280.526,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "renewable energy, it’s clear that",
        "start": 282.446,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "people are working on solutions",
        "start": 284.606,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "such as energy storage to make",
        "start": 286.206,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "sure there is always a supply.",
        "start": 288.446,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "And that computers can be used to",
        "start": 290.846,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "design and operate technology",
        "start": 292.366,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "as efficiently as possible.",
        "start": 294.286,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Much in the same way that AI can",
        "start": 296.286,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "be used in your home to make it",
        "start": 298.206,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "run as efficiently as possible.",
        "start": 300.046,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "Yes – all in the hope of",
        "start": 302.366,
        "duration": 1.12
    },
    {
        "text": "reducing your carbon footprint.",
        "start": 303.486,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "Which reminds me of your quiz question, Neil.",
        "start": 305.566,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "Yes, in my quiz question I asked Sam",
        "start": 308.446,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "how many tonnes of carbon dioxide",
        "start": 310.686,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "humans produce each year!",
        "start": 312.766,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "I went for b) 40 billion tonnes.",
        "start": 315.006,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "Which is… the correct answer!",
        "start": 318.126,
        "duration": 1.2
    },
    {
        "text": "Well done, Sam!",
        "start": 319.326,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "Wow – I guessed right – but all three",
        "start": 320.846,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "of those numbers sound really high!",
        "start": 323.326,
        "duration": 2.854
    },
    {
        "text": "Let’s recap the vocabulary from today’s",
        "start": 326.18,
        "duration": 1.786
    },
    {
        "text": "programme about smart tech and",
        "start": 327.966,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "climate change, starting with",
        "start": 329.966,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "dig something up – an informal expression",
        "start": 332.206,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "which means to remove something from the ground.",
        "start": 335.326,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "Intermittent is used to describe something",
        "start": 338.286,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "that is not continuous or steady.",
        "start": 340.366,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "Blackouts are periods of time without",
        "start": 343.326,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "energy, for example electricity.",
        "start": 345.886,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "In real time means without delay or live.",
        "start": 348.206,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "Machine learning is the process by which",
        "start": 351.806,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "computers learn and change",
        "start": 354.286,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "behaviour based on data.",
        "start": 356.126,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "And finally, simulate means",
        "start": 358.606,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": "produce a computer model.",
        "start": 360.366,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "That’s all for this programme.",
        "start": 362.526,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "Bye for now!",
        "start": 364.046,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "Goodbye!",
        "start": 365.566,
        "duration": 1.22
    }
]